National Vision Party (NVP) leader Nicholas Biwott has endorsed Deputy President William Ruto for the 2022 elections. The former Cabinet Minister urged the Kalenjin community to back Ruto and President Uhuru Kenyatta in next year&rsquo;s General Election. Biwott said there was no political competition for the DP position among the Kalenjin community, adding that he will work with other leaders in supporting the DP&rsquo;s presidential bid. &ldquo;I want to declare, we as the Kalenjin community have only one leader and that is Ruto. We will support him both in 2017 and 2022,&rdquo; he said. He said the country had tremendous development projects under the Jubilee administration. READ MORE Leaders want 500 acres hived off multinational tea firms' land Biwot endorses DP Ruto for 2022 presidential bid Ruto targets tea firms in land row